<h2>Event in May 2018</h2>
<h3>Torrential rain and thunderstorms on 13 May 2018</h3>
<br><br>
A high-altitude trough approached Western Europe and warm subtropical air was advected.
This warm humid air collided with cold air from the north. At the trailing edge of the frontal zone a convergence line was formed with a wind jump, extending from the North-East of the Netherlands to the Austrian border. Where the different air masses met, the air was forced to ascend which induced convection and thunderstorms along the convergence line.
<br><br>
The thunderstorms produced many strikes, heavy rainfall and hail. In some places over 30 mm of rain fell within one hour. At Winterberg in Sauerland a centimeter-high layer of hail was reported. Due to the low altitude current, the convergence line was almost stationary and the precipitation area only shifted very slowly, causing torrential rain in this area. Further away from the frontal zone, little to no rain was observed.
<br><br>
Due to the heavy thunderstorms with its intense precipitation, streets and basements were flooded, and in Ostfriesland a music festival was cancelled. On the roads there were traffic obstructions, so the A30 between Hannover and Amsterdam was completely closed for a short time due to floods. Also, the flight plan in Cologne/Bonn airport was affected due to the storm. Air planes were re-directed to surrounding airports.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/may2018/European_climate_20180513bli01.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/may2018/European_climate_20180513bli01.png" width="300px"></a>
<br><br>
<em>Figure 1: Number of lightning strikes during 13 May 2018 (source Blitzortung.org)</em>
<br><br>
<h2>Specific climate indicators for May 2018</h2>
In most of Europe the number of warm days was larger than in the reference period 1981-2010 (Figure 2). As ’warm’ relates to the >90 percentile range, the reference number of warm days per month is about 3. The number of warm days was particularly large in The Netherlands, northern Germany, and southern Scandinavia. In parts of these regions there were in this month more than 20 warm days. In southern Europa the number of warm days was small, with even no warm days in parts of Spain and Portugal.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg90p_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_TG90p_baselayers_overlay_2018-05-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg90p_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_TG90p_baselayers_overlay_2018-05-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg90p_2018_month_nc__2018-05-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg90p_2018_month_nc__2018-05-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<br><br>
<em>Figure 2: TG90p: Days with TG > 90th percentile (warm days) in May 2018</em>
<br><br>
The highest temperatures in Europe in May 2018 occurred in The Netherlands, Northern Germany, and parts of Eastern Europe. Here the maximum of daily maximum temperature values was larger than 30 &#176;C (Figure 3). In The Netherlands May 2018 was the warmest May since the beginning of the regular temperature observations in 1706.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_txx_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_TXx_baselayers_overlay_2018-05-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_txx_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_TXx_baselayers_overlay_2018-05-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_txx_2018_month_nc__2018-05-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_txx_2018_month_nc__2018-05-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<br><br>
<em>Figure 3: TXx: Maximum of daily maximum temperature in May 2018</em>
<br><br>
The number of summer days, with a maximum temperature more than 25 &#176;C, is shown in Figure 4. Large values of more than 12 summer days occurred in Central Europe, Ukraine, The Netherlands and northern Germany.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_su_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_SU_baselayers_overlay_2018-05-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/may2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_su_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_SU_baselayers_overlay_2018-05-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
