<h2>The weather in May 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
Daily minimum, average and maximum temperatures were exceptionally above average over almost all of Central, Northern and Eastern Europe in May 2018. Temperatures were near average in the south of France, Spain, Portugal and Greece and only below average in the southwest of Spain and south of Portugal. In Portugal and Spain the temperatures of the coldest night and warmest day were much below, locally even exceptionally below average. Large parts of Germany also recorded below average coldest night temperatures, due to clear skies under high pressure influence.
